  "summary": "Finland's annual happiness score for 2025 (to be reported in the 2026 WHR, due March 20, 2026) is forecasted based on derived annual scores from 2016-2024. The historical range is 7.660-7.889, with the 2024 score at 7.781. Three simulation models (normal random walk, bootstrap, AR(1)) converge on a median around 7.79. Finland's economy was weak in 2025 (near-stagnation, 9.4% unemployment), but historically happiness scores have been highly resilient to economic downturns. The distribution is narrow, reflecting the very low volatility of this metric (std of annual changes ≈ 0.092).",
